content: Excellent supplemental resource for studying
Although few questions are repeated from sybex 8th edition not worth to purchase this app as it contains same questions giving high ratings so that the review comes up
The App is crashing while using Flash cards. Other things are good till now.
Found the app to be quite useful to so a quick refresh of concepts by topic and take up assessments while on the move.

I had hoped the questions would be different than those in the book. Also, they are not dynamic in that once you complete the practice 40... there are no more new questions. For $20 I expected a huge database of prep questions.
replyContent: Hi Stephanie, The assessment test has only 40 questions, but there are many more questions in the app. Go to Custom Test Builder to create tests with many more questions. Please reach out to us at support@learnzapp.com, if you have any questions/suggestions. Regards.

content: Needs bigger question bank for the app, needs better explanations for answers

Just completed exam and these questions are nothing like the ones I had. Vastly overpriced. Full of American questions wholly irrelevant to anywhere else in the world. Some questions like "which of the runner-up AES standards uses..." demonstrate that this is created by people showing off how clever they think they are.

Good study tool. Obviously not for your primary study material for the test. It has a ton of recourses to cement your learning, like flashcards, quizes, topic based assessments, and a long assessments that tells you why the answer is correct. The only thing I have against the app, is for the main assessment. I just wish it would have different questions for the "assessment test" that's about it tho.
Great tool with a variety of ways to test. The bookmarks and custom tests are extremely helpful

App was very helpful when treated not as the only source of information and practice. The app provided quality flash cards and practice questions to use quickly. It would have been convenient if it could be easily used on the desktop as well.
Insufficient for preparing for the test on its own, but all the right topics are covered, so a more in-depth understanding of those topics through additional study allowed me to pass the CISSP!

In the app, question 14 is incorrect. what is the primary goal of change management. The app says the answer is to prevent security compromises, however in the official cissp sybex book 8th edition on page 18 it states "its primary purpose is to make all changes subject to detailed documentation and auditing". So the answer in the app should be to main documentation. please fix.
Great App...

Just not useful at all. Flashcards and answers are mostly meaningless and 
that's pretty much all ya get. Just stick to free websites and a 
book...don't waste $ on this poorly done app.
Easy to use app; however, questions are nothing like they are on the actual certification test. Far better off buying the Shin Harris book and using that test bank to gauge your knowledge.
Get it!
Great app. Wish the flashcards broke some concepts down into smaller process. Just passed using this app as a supplement to a couple books and the other ISC app.
Very Helpful for the preparation of CISSP

Includes only the questions from the SYBEX source material book. Not a single question that isn't.  I could have hand written the answers and gotten as much out of the book instead of spending â‚¬7 on the app. I actually did. They have repackaged the same questions twice and charged for them each time.
Includes questions on content that doesn't appear in the current version of the Official CBK such as US laws, US military classifications and licensing types.
Good sets of questions. Lots more could be done to improve the UI and help identify concepts that you are deficient in.
While doing mock test the questions randomly jumps without reading and finishes the test
Keeps  stopping on Android 8
Helpful study alternative.
Very little content. Just some flashcards (which does not explain the concept well) and a few questions.
Perfect for revise during travel.
Good for on the move or waiting room studying

I have a Samsung S7. You can not view the entire questions in this app. You can only view the bottom half and the answer. I have tried to move to different questions and had the same result. How can you answer a question only seeing half the question?

It's OK, don't base you study and final prep off of this app. With a limited amount of questions (relative to other products on the market) and lacking a full practice test it left a lot to be desired during test prep.
Questions are copies of what's in the book. Display is skewed so much I had to quit using it. Support not responsive
Failed test...these questions are not focus or deep enough to prepare you for the actual test
One minor issue: In portrait mode, when the question number is 100 or higher, the green header cuts off the top of the question.
Pretty solid. I'd highlight the key terms within the flashcards. Example: highlight "integrity'  when defining it.
Great way to prepare for the test.
Weird layout, please make more clear the separation between the type of tests and the domains.
Please update your app with more questions. The content can be further improved. Questions can be segregated by difficulty level.
Passed the test! This app is very worth it for the practice tests alone.

This is great for on-the-go and spur of the moment studying, but it contains exactly the same questions as the book i had already purchased. Would have been nice to know that in advance. It foiled some of my study plans as well, because i had planned on taking a practice test from the book later, but had already been through the questions at that point.
The convenience of this app is great. The app has helped me to find moments to study when I didn't think I had the time.
Very good app on the go when you don't have the book with you. Hopefully the exam will have similar questions.
Contains exactly the same questions as the book, down to the typos, so not very valuable since you probably already have the book. Functionality is nothing special. Definitely not worth $10.
Amazing help! Let's me know what domains I need to work on and which ones I already know.
Decent app. Can't exit, scrolls back to cards you were viewing. Needs exit option.
Best value for CISSP app and most like the actual questions on test. Only wish that you could randomize the questions or pick from domains to create own quiz.
Content is fine, but app is very unresponsive when making test and reviewing answers. Can take up to 5 seconds to show the next question after swiping, making it frustrating to use.
This app just got tons better by the addition of random and multiple questions! Great job!
A very good tool to practice the tests while on the move...
I wish that the section tests had a pool of random questions

Passed the test. Great app for studying when you'd normally be reading news or playing games. Don't rely on this as your only study material though. I had an issue with my Nexus 5 where the answers would disappear. The developer was friendly professional and just released an update (less than a week later). Worth the money.
Ties in with the official book, an excellent resource for the price

I was hoping for something a little more extensive, with a little more material than what was offered for the application. I would have gladly paid more for the more extensive application that helps to study for the CISSP exam.  It's true that a person gets what they pay for, and for a study application with as much material as what the Certification covers, I think I would have been willing to pay up to $50 for a very good study application with extensive study material covered within for this particular certification exam. That said, it's decent for the $10 the that a person pays for it.
The flashcards are somewhat useful. The questions are identical as ones in book.
Good
Good job!
Great app
Grat questions.  Like the way it gives you feedback for incorrect answers.

Pros- official app should provide the most accurate possible question bank  Cons- app itself feels immature and lacking as a study tool.  I still prefer PocketPrep which provides immediate feedback, includes metrics and much nicer overall.
Good app for quick test while on the go.
I recommend this App as I have seen upto 50% of similar questions cane in my exam..! Good Luck..!

This application is great for supplemental studying. Do not rely on it alone to pass the test I'm sure it was not meant for that purpose. I'll be taking that my exam in a few weeks and feel very confident
Effective, essentially a digital version of book test questions.
Please include more sample questions for practice. There is lack of scenario based questions.
Pretty good for revising concepts!

I'm not a Candy Crush, phone playing kind of person. But, I can't put it down. It's not necessarily new, intriguing hacker V. spook kinda information. Just very well done and addictive. Now if only the actual test was so easy!!
This helps to keep focus on CISSP content whenever have few spare minutes. I got used to gray GUI after few weeks.
Quizzes don't show why wrong answers are wrong and flash cards are very limited
very helpful for preparation
But wish it retained a history of scores and let you return to unfinished or accidentally exited tests.
This app keeps cissp information easily at your fingertips
I'd like for the flash card to be automated. Where you can set a timer and the answer pops up automatically.
I used this app with a conviction of other resources and passed CISSP from the first try
A God-send, very practical and allows me to study anywhere. I love it!!!
Helps with quick review and Q&N
The app is very good and I used it for a quick study all the time before the test.
I hope the questions are representative of what's on the test.  Given the reputation of this certification, the questions don't seem very difficult.
Questioning
Great tool to go along with study for CISSP Exam
The app is very practical and allows to quickly review the key topics and to test own preparation.
App provides additional level of study with explanation of answer.   Uses older version of the  cissp cbk.

App is good with flash cards and answers for each chapter as given at the end of each chapter in the book. Also there are mini tests and mock tests that will help you in understanding the exams and as well as in assessing your capabilities for exam
Too few questions. Style of questions close to those in the exam. Easy to use.
So far so good
Excellent for preparing for the final exam. Along with reference materials.
Let's see if I pass.
Good questions (wish there were more) in an easy to use format.

This is study guide app is right in line with the Sybex online test bank. This app is great for on the go. I mostly used this app to maximize tge day with studying. Whenever, I was on break or waiting around I would open this app. This was better than surfing twitter and facebook. The mock test were short and sweet. This app is amazing

I found the app useful for reviewing topics when I had just a few minutes, like when waiting for meetings to start. I was disappointed in the flashcards - some of them provided details, but many indicate topics you need to know, without any details on the topics themselves.
clean, neat

I have this app on iPhone and Android. The iPhone version is more stable than the Android version. For some reason this version started flickering and not showing the answers while I was taking one of the assessment test. The only way I was able to see the screen was to close the app or minimize it and reopen it for each question. I'm currently using a Nexus 5
Now I can sneak in prep work while on line to check out, while in boring meetings or with a few extra minutes available.
This will help you study for the exam if you're on the go.  It also makes taking the practice questions at the end of the chapters much more convenient.
Will be better if you could download additional questions

Aplikasinya Bagus, Membantu Memahami Keseluruhan Chapter di Bukunya, Karena disediakan Flashcard serta Soal dan Pembahasan di Setiap Chapternya.. Namun Sayang Saya Gagal di Ujian Kemarin (10102016) Cuma Dapat Skor 601 dari 1000.. passing Grade 700.. 250 Soal dalam Waktu 6 Jam..
I passed the exam in September and found the app to be a solid resource for reviewing key concepts of each domain and most importantly practice questions.
Obviously this should not be the official app for the certification.
I use this app to refresh my memory when I have a lapse....works great!
Good app, needs to add some of the drag and dro items from the test

Awesome app! Flashcards are great, gives you ideas on what you need to research and become more familiar with. For the questions, it's fantastic that the explanation of not only the right answer is given, but why it is right and why the other options are incorrect.
Useful
Great app for CISSP prep

Great app for those who are studying for the CISSP.  Just one suggestion though.  Implement a random function with the flashcards and questions.  People have a tendency of memorizing the same thing if repeated enough times.  Key to CISSP should be to know the information not to memorize it.  Again, though, great app!

Here are a few areas where it does great. 1. The test questions are worded with some complexity just as in the exam. 2. Test reviews show the correct answer with an explanation. 3. Timed test exercise helps assess your speed per question, extremely helpful in the exam.   Hoping the app gets progress tracking to help see improvement over time. Not a big issue.

I passed the exam on the first try. However, you should NOT expect to just do the questions in this app and pass. I read the Sybex book (that the app is based on) cover to cover, did a bunch of sample questions that came with the book, have worked in the industry for over 10 years, and took a one week boot camp before sitting the exam. I'd recommend at least the book, the sample questions and the app if you want to have a decent chance of passing. It's a tough test.
Great tool on the go
same questions from the sybex study guide
Awesome! 10$ worth
Just another user
I love this app, it appears to be helpful so far, although I've only been using it for a few days...
Just keep in mind this doesn't match the official ISC study guide. The chapters don't match. For example in the official book section 3 is System Security  (i.e. Encryption ).
I can lay in bed while other are sleeping and clock some study time for the day
This is set up nicely to challenge you and help you learn
I passed. Study what the flash cards tell you to study. Beyond just what the flashcards say. They are spot on.
Good

So far is very good source of info. I have app on my phone and have been studying and testing instead of wasting time on FB. I took CISSP boot camp and I took the CISSP test and did not pass yet. This app has lots of good, useful info you will want to know before testing.
Very thorough and relevant questions. Could just use some of the new formatting that the new cissp questions sometimes feature.
Excellent app to go along with the Sybex CISSP 7th book and cccure question bank.  GREAT!!!
Very useful for reviewing key concepts. I highly recommend it.

Great if the authors could include explanations for all possible answers to give a better understanding why it was the best answer. The questions followed after each section ideally could be revised to the mock exam style.

Just got the app but it pairs with reading the official text by Sybex well. Flashcards and questions are great. Haven't tried the tests yet though. But I used this company's Security+ app extensively before taking that test and passed it the first time. I'm one month away from my CISSP boot camp and exam. So I am hoping this app and book supplement the gaps in my work experience and professional knowledge. Seems to be doing the trick so far!
Close to perfection. I would like a cleaner yet more beautiful design. The current layout leaves much to be desired but gets the job done.

Really find this app useful to test yourself with questions across multiple domains  and helps you to reinforce your concepts where you are wrong with your answers.
For the novice preparing for the CISSP exam the flash cards can be viewed as an excellent refresher helping one remembering key concepts and terminologies.  The language is simple and to the point.
This app is the best,  simple,  easy,  light weight and the best to accompany any book. Sybex 7rh edition is now in hands for a review.  Love the app and really a great job.  Bravoo thumbs up high
The questions from this book will not prepare you for the exam nor will this app.
